com.mousebird.maply

Interface VectorStyle

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    VectorStyleSimpleGenerator.VectorStyleSimple, VectorStyleSimpleGenerator.VectorStyleSimpleLinear, VectorStyleSimpleGenerator.VectorStyleSimplePoint, VectorStyleSimpleGenerator.VectorStyleSimplePolygon

    public interface VectorStyle
    A VectorStyle subclass generates the Maply objects for a given pieces of data. This is used by the MapboxVectorTileSource to turn vector tile data into visible objects. Potentially it can be used by other sources as well since there's no dependency on vector tiles.

    • Method Detail

      • getUuid

        java.lang.String getUuid()
        Return a unique identifier for your style. This is used to help shortcut data processing.

      • geomIsAdditive

        boolean geomIsAdditive()
        Set if this geometry is additive (e.g. sticks around) rather than being replaced.

      • buildObjects

        ComponentObject[] buildObjects(java.util.List<VectorObject> objects,
                               MaplyTileID tileID,
                               MaplyBaseController controller)
        Construct objects related to this style based on the input data. This is where we build the visible objects for the data corresponding to our style.
        Parameters:
        objects - The vector objects we'll build a visual representation for.
        tileID - The tile we're building, if this is used by a tile source. If not, this is null.
        controller - The MaplyBaseController to use when building the visual representation.
        Returns:
        The ComponentObjects created when building a visual representation.
